AGENT SemanticObservable
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Provide a frozen intent rubric and a signed coherence scorer for semantic alignment measurement
GOAL Enforce CANNOT_MUTATE on the scoring rubric at runtime — no LLM regeneration
     Measure text coherence across the three trajectory stages
     Emit a signed observable signal per run for Sovereign consumption
     Maintain append-only semantic log across sessions

RECEIVES stage_texts: list, run_id: string, prompt_hash: string, hmac_key: bytes
EMITS semantic_signal: dict
MUTATES observable_log_file
CANNOT_MUTATE rubric, rubric_version, threshold, coherence_formula, drift_formula,
              stopword_list, tokenization_rules, signing_algorithm, append_only_contract

CONSTRAINT RUBRIC is a frozen mapping from IntentType to ConditionSet — no runtime mutation allowed
CONSTRAINT ConditionSet threshold is fixed at 0.65 for every intent type
CONSTRAINT Every IntentType entry must have at least two success conditions and one failure condition
CONSTRAINT Runtime assignment to RUBRIC, ConditionSet fields, or Condition fields raises ImmutabilityViolation
CONSTRAINT Stage texts list must contain exactly three entries
CONSTRAINT Each stage text must be a non-empty string
CONSTRAINT Non-string stage text raises SemanticTypeError
CONSTRAINT Coherence is mean cosine similarity between consecutive stage term vectors
CONSTRAINT Drift is one minus coherence
CONSTRAINT Direction is stable when drift below drift threshold, drifting otherwise
CONSTRAINT Every emitted signal is HMAC-SHA256 signed producing sixty-four character hex
CONSTRAINT Observable log is append-only

RULES
- Define IntentType enum with ask_boolean, ask_causal, ask_medical, ask_factual, ask_recommendation, ask_procedural
- Define Condition with text, weight, condition_type fields frozen against mutation
- Define ConditionSet with conditions list and threshold frozen against mutation
- Define RUBRIC as frozen mapping of IntentType to ConditionSet
- Set RUBRIC_VERSION constant to 1.0.0
- On any attempt to assign to RUBRIC keys or ConditionSet or Condition fields: raise ImmutabilityViolation
- Accept exactly three stage texts for preflight, mid_chain, final_synthesis
- Validate: reject if count not three, reject if any entry is not a string, reject if any entry is empty
- Tokenize each stage text: lowercase, remove punctuation, remove stopwords
- Build term frequency vector for each tokenized stage
- Compute cosine similarity between preflight and mid_chain vectors
- Compute cosine similarity between mid_chain and final_synthesis vectors
- Coherence score is mean of both similarities rounded to six decimal places
- Drift score is one minus coherence rounded to six decimal places
- Select dominant topic as most frequent non-stopword term across all stage texts
- Classify direction as stable when drift below drift threshold, drifting otherwise
- Build signal dict with all required fields and HMAC signature
- Append signal to observable log as single UTF-8 JSON line
- Emit signed signal dict to caller

PROCESS
- Receive three stage texts and run identification fields
- Validate stage count equals three, each entry is a non-empty string
- Tokenize each stage removing punctuation and stopwords
- Compute term frequency vector per stage
- Compute consecutive cosine similarities
- Compute coherence and drift from similarities
- Select dominant topic
- Determine direction
- Build unsigned signal payload
- Sign with keyed SHA-256 via hexdigest
- Append to log
- Emit signal

CHECK
- Stage list with count not equal to three is rejected before processing
- Empty string at any stage is rejected before processing
- Non-string at any stage is rejected before processing
- Identical texts produce coherence of one and drift of zero
- Incoherent texts produce coherence below half and direction drifting
- Signal contains run_id, prompt_hash, coherence_score, drift_score, direction, dominant_topic, stage_similarities, timestamp, signature
- Signature is sixty-four character hex
- RUBRIC assignment raises ImmutabilityViolation
- ConditionSet field assignment raises ImmutabilityViolation
- Condition field assignment raises ImmutabilityViolation
- RUBRIC_VERSION equals 1.0.0
- Every intent has threshold 0.65
- Every intent has at least two success conditions and one failure condition

WHEN
- observe_request: activate ComputeCoherence
- validation_failure: activate InputError
- mutation_attempt: activate ImmutabilityViolation
- signal_ready: activate AppendLog

FAILURE
- On stage count not three: raise SemanticStageError with expected count
- On empty stage text: raise SemanticInputError identifying position
- On non-string stage text: raise SemanticTypeError identifying position
- On RUBRIC or ConditionSet or Condition mutation attempt: raise ImmutabilityViolation
- On signing failure: append signal without signature and log signing error
- On log write failure: report error, signal still returned to caller

CONCEPT FrozenRubric
PURPOSE Provide a deterministic, immutable scoring rubric that cannot be regenerated or altered at runtime
APPLIES WHEN scoring-request rubric-access
NOT WHEN rubric-mutation-attempted
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES all ConditionSet and Condition objects reject attribute assignment
REQUIRES RUBRIC mapping rejects key assignment
REQUIRES threshold fixed at 0.65 across all intents
EFFECT scoring is deterministic across all runs — no LLM regeneration possible

CONCEPT CoherenceScorer
PURPOSE Measure semantic agreement between consecutive reasoning stage texts
APPLIES WHEN three-valid-stage-texts provided
NOT WHEN validation-failed
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES term frequency vectors computed from stopword-filtered tokenized text
REQUIRES cosine similarity computed between consecutive stage vectors
REQUIRES coherence as mean similarity, drift as complement
EFFECT semantic coherence observable produced for Sovereign consumption

CONCEPT ObservableLog
PURPOSE Maintain append-only tamper-resistant record of semantic signals across sessions
APPLIES WHEN signal-signed-and-ready
NOT WHEN signing-failed
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES log opened in append mode never write mode
REQUIRES each entry is a single valid UTF-8 JSON line
EFFECT Sovereign can audit full semantic history without accessing internal reasoning state

OUTPUT
- semantic signal: dict with run_id, prompt_hash, coherence_score, drift_score,
                   direction, dominant_topic, stage_similarities, timestamp,
                   module, signature
- observable log entry: HMAC-signed JSONL record appended per run

SUCCESS
rubric_immutability:    0.30
coherence_accuracy:     0.25
drift_classification:   0.25
sovereign_readability:  0.20
